name: iffah cothem
review: (Translated by Google) I don't know if it's the same place or different. The name is the same but I see the photos are different from the results of my visit there. When I got there the place had two floors. Direct entry to the second floor. The collection is incomplete and the first floor is empty. When I bought spring rolls, I ran out of sauce or gravy. Then I asked, you don't get chili? The answer is, it's finished, can't make it anymore. I canceled, but because I was not alone, the sambal was finally made. Even though the spring rolls there are not cheap, 10 thousand/pcs. Depends on the content. There are 15 thousand / pcs too. For me it's delicious. I like. Apart from that, other services are good and friendly too. Oh yes, the one at the spring roll stand was friendly too. If we have a lot of ole-ole, we can ask for cardboard wrappers. It's only enough to add 5 thousand if I remember correctly. The other floor is quiet. There is a cafe but when I went there it was very quiet, there were no people at all. Is it still closed, I don't know. There is a children's play area, but it's also closed. Maybe this is all the effects of a long Pandemic. Hope you get back up soon.. Spirit! (Original) Entah ini tempat yang sama atau berbeda. Namanya sama tapi saya lihat foto-fotonya berbeda dengan hasil kunjungan saya kesana. Waktu kesana tempatnya berlantai dua. Masuknya langsung ke lantai dua. Koleksinya kurang lengkap dan lantai satu kosong. Waktu beli lumpia, sempat kehabisan sambal atau kuah. Terus saya tanya, loh nggak dapat sambal? Jawabannya,sudah habis tidak bisa bikin lagi. Saya cancel, namun karena saya tidak sendirian akhirnya dibuatkanlah sambalnya. Padahal lumpiah di sana itu tidak murah loh, 10rb/pcs. Tergantung isi. Ada yg 15rb/pcs juga. Bagi saya sih enak. Saya suka. Selain itu, pelayanan lainnya baik dan ramah juga. Oh ya, yang di stand lumpia tadi ramah juga kok. Kalau ole-ole kita banyak, bisa minta bungkus kardus. Hanya cukup nambah 5rb kalau Ndak salah ingat. Lantai satunya sepi. Ada cafe tapi waktu saya kesana sepi banget, nggak ada orang sama sekali. Apa masih tutup ya saya kurang tahu. Ada tempat mainan anak, tapi tutup juga. Mungkin ini semua efek Pandemi yang panjang. Semoga segera bangkit kembali ya.. Semangat!

name: Dee Deandri
review: (Translated by Google) Every return trip from Jogja / Solo to Jakarta, he always makes time to stop by Semarang, and one of the destinations is the Djoe Souvenir Center. Wednesday, May 4, 2022, for the fourth time came here just to buy his Loenpia. The price is a bit expensive, but treated with a very good taste. The best 'Loenpia Semarang' in town!! The drawback (very disappointing) is that buying 5 loenpias is the same as buying 1 loenpia, because you only get 1 very small amount of sauce along with green onions & cayenne pepper, not worth the amount of loenpia you buy. Experience teaches that when asking for extra sauce, it will not be given even though the extra sauce will be paid for. The seller's reason is because it is according to the owner's directions. Very very disappointing, because 1 small packet of sauce with very little content is only enough for 1-2 loenpia which are quite large and the filling is dense (a lot). As a result, buying 10 special loenpia (@ Rp20,000,-) was only given 2 small packets of very little sauce along with green onions & cayenne pepper. Hopefully in the future it will be the owner's consideration to provide an adequate amount of sauce, because the price of loenpia is expensive, the buyer is entitled to the appropriate amount of sauce. For example, for the purchase of 2 loenpia, 1 sauce is given, and so on according to the multiples. Or if you want to add sauce, you have to buy it at a certain price. (Original) Setiap perjalanan pulang dari Jogja / Solo menuju Jakarta selalu menyempatkan mampir ke Semarang, dan salah satu tujuannya adalah Pusat Oleh-Oleh Djoe. Rabu, 4 Mei 2022, untuk keempat kalinya datang ke sini hanya untuk membeli Loenpia - nya. Harganya agak mahal, tetapi terobati dengan rasanya yang enak banget. The best â€˜Loenpia Semarangâ€™ in town!! Kekurangannya (sangat mengecewakan) adalah membeli 5 buah loenpia sama saja dengan membeli 1 buah loenpia, karena hanya mendapatkan 1 buah saus dalam jumlah yang sangat sedikit beserta daun bawang & cabe rawit hijau, tidak sebanding dengan jumlah loenpia yang dibeli. Pengalaman mengajarkan bahwa ketika meminta tambahan saus, tidak akan diberikan walaupun tambahan sausnya akan dibayar. Alasan penjual karena hal itu sesuai arahan owner. Sangat sangat mengecewakan, karena 1 bungkus kecil saus yang sangat sedikit isinya itu hanya cukup untuk 1-2 buah loenpianya yang berukuran lumayan besar dan isiannya padat (banyak). Alhasil, membeli 10 buah loenpia special (@ Rp20.000,-) hanya diberikan 2 bungkus kecil saus yang sangat sedikit isinya beserta daun bawang & cabe rawit hijau. Semoga ke depannya menjadi pertimbangan owner untuk memberikan jumlah saus yang memadai, karena harga loenpia-nya termasuk mahal, pembeli berhak mendapatkan jumlah saus yang sesuai. Misalnya untuk pembelian 2 loenpia diberikan 1 saus, dan seterusnya sesuai dengan kelipatannya. Atau jika ingin menambah saus harus membeli dengan harga tertentu.

name: Antotik 17
review: (Translated by Google) Ayu shop, that's the name the center of Semarang's typical souvenirs. Kedai Ayu is located in Pudak Payung, just before entering the city gate of Ungaran, or it can be said as the border between Semarang City and Semarang Regency. Kedai Ayu does provide snacks for typical souvenirs from Semarang, one of which is Lumpia Semarang. so if you want to bring some souvenirs and don't have time to look for it in the city of Semarang, then Kedai Ayu is the right choice. the parking lot is quite wide too. Anyway, if you want to eat too, it's also available here. (Original) kedai Ayu, demikian namanya tempat pusat oleh-oleh khas Semarang. Kedai Ayu terletak di Pudak Payung, tepat sebelum memasuki gerbang kota Ungaran, atau bisa dikatakan sebagai perbatasan Kota Semarang dengan Kabupaten Semarang. Kedai Ayu memang menyediakan makanan-makanan ringan untuk oleh-oleh khas dari Semarang, salah satunya adalah Lumpia Semarang. jadi kalau kalian mau bawa oleh-oleh dan tidak sempat cari di kota Semarang, maka Kedai Ayu adalah pilihan yang tepat. tempat parkiran cukup luas juga. oya, kalau hendak makan pun, di sini juga tersedia koq.

name: Elizabeth Jonatan
review: Best place to have souvenirs and authentic javanese snacks and food from Semarang, their variant sells of milkfish is many so you can choose based on ur preferences. This store also big.

name: Gede Bagus Bayu Pentium
review: This is one of the favourite places to get Bandeng Juwana. The taste is guaranteed to be good, I've tried this place multiple times. But because it's popular the place is always crowded and has a very long queue. Maybe not worth the time to queue. If you don't have time, you can visit other stores around with a lesser queue. The taste is sometimes not much different

name: elmo rinaldi
review: A favorite place to buy local culinary like Bandeng Presto and other snack. Located near central downtown and at main road, this store is easy to find. Try their Bandeng Otak-Otak. The best. However, the parking space is very small and the pedestrian is packed with other seller.

name: Jeffrey Tanujaya
review: The place to buy bandeng presto in Semarang. Be prepared for the long queue. There is a small restaurant on the 2nd floor if you want to have cooked bandeng on the spot.

name: Arya Pradana
review: One stop shopping for food souvenir in Semarang, placed near simpang lima and lawang sewu. accept all digital payment. the bad thing, parking was very difficult everytime

name: Jovellina Verbi Dei Minister
review: Your visit to Semarang is not completed without bandeng presto but here is one of famous store between many other stores in Pandanaran area. Actually here is quite expensive but it provides many various options including other products that can brought as oleh oleh. You can eat on site in higher level. The staffs are friendly and helpful. They serve fast too.

name: Yoppie Widianto
review: Tasty Bandeng Presto. The best place to buy Bandeng Prestos Fish. And this place have some other Snack.

name: Irhas Badruzaman
review: Buy your semarang snack and the famous bandeng fresto. There are many kind of bandeng presto here. There was also the resto on second floor if you eant to try dirextly the delicacy.

name: Imam Santosa
review: This food souvenirs+resto store is located at Jalan Pandanaran. They offer lots of local food from Semarang and around such as Bandeng, Wingko Babad, Lumpia and Mochi. Snacks or food are very various. They have lots of staff and they are mostly well trained. Could be very crowded during weekend. So hot inside since they have only fan to cools the room temperature. Parking is a big challenge. Restaurant is available at the second floor. Offering mostly local dish with bandeng as the highlight such as asem asem bandeng, bandeng kuah tauco, sate bandeng etc. Toilet and musholla are available

name: Jesslyn Christiana
review: It's one of the biggest souvenir centres in Semarang, has varieties of food products from all over Central Java, located near the city centre. Car park is very crowded, so you might need to walk a bit to reach the destination, but be careful of cars since it's located on the side of the road. The staple product is milkfish of all kinds, but if you're looking for trinkets souvenir, there's none inside, however, on the side of the road, there are a few small vendors who sell souvenir t-shirts and trinkets.

name: Irwan Hidayatullah
review: So crowdedd.. many choices of oleh2 khas Semarang ! Specially Bandeng Juwana in many forms!ğŸ˜‚There are also restaurant at second floor !

name: Sylvia Rini Handayani
review: Located in the heart of Semarang, this place is heaven for Semarang food souvenirs / oleh-oleh! The biggest store has every Semarang unique food you need. Bandeng, Lunpia, wingko - of all varieties with different promotions and bonuses. Becareful, you may leave this place with empty wallet:p. The food are very affordable, and quick services, too. Some food have testers served. The staffs are very helpful and friendly, thumbs up!! All u need to do is stroll the street and browse everything! I dont see toilets here so you might as well be prepared.

name: JD Pranata
review: So many authentic Semarang foods were sold in here. Its speciality is in Bandeng fish: presto, asap/smoke, otak-otak, etc.It also sell moci Semarang.

name: Arman Pramono
review: Really a must buy snacks stores in semarang. Never miss come here when in Semarang. They specialize in many kinds of bandeng, taste really great. The most common is bandeng duri lunak. They also sell other snacks. Parking a bit difficult and inside is crowded.

name: Bastanta Lubis
review: Place where you can find local food from Semarang, main menu is Bandeng presto (milkfish pressure) so the bone is soft. But there is no only bandeng, they have a lot of snack salty (lunpia etc) and sweet snacks. Place is so crowded and hot, not a place to bring kids there.

name: Hapsarina Dianti
review: You have so many choices of meal and all taste great! I regret nothing since it's all taste so good. The downside is, I placed on the upper floor since the ground floor full for the shop, so elderly need assist here. But the stairs not that high so it's save.

name: Nurul Aini Fadilah
review: It located in the central of town, near Lawang Sewu and Poncol Train Station. Along the road, there are also a lot of similar shop, but this is the most famous of all. They have many iconic food of Semarang, Bandeng Presto, Lumpia, Wingko Babat, and other like Moci, a lot of snacks and cracker, Bakpia, Enting, Abon, Cakes, and a lot more. Its famous with the good quality and taste, so people dont doubt to pay more. They have some cashier so customer dont have to queue too long. But the parking area is limited, car have to park on road side.

name: Lobelia Asmaul Husna
review: You can get as much as gift to your lovely ones after visit semarang in this place. I don't try the food so far, but it seems good.

name: Dela
review: The restaurant is on 2nd floor. They have wide variety of mikfish here. The restaurant is very clean, the staffs are friendly and helpful with good knowledge of menu, their milkfish is totally fresh and tender! Superbbbb

name: Langga Calvareno
review: very good place to get authentic javanese food and snack from Semarang The place is small, but still neat and comfortable The parking space is quite small, so maybe it will be hard to park your car

name: Erlin Tirto
review: Still a good place to buy smoked bandeng oleh oleh. You have to go early in their first open time to avoid a crowded people and parking issue

name: Muhammad Arief Rahman
review: best local souvenirs in semarang. love it. you must try the bandeng presto, best in the town!

name: YAN YAN PELIYANA
review: It's a place which have to visit when you need to buy original food from Semarang. Very complete with affordable price. At second level of those place, you can find some ready to eat traditional food from Semarang

name: Ekaprana Daniswara
review: One of the famous gift shop in town, the "Bandeng" is good-taste although only edible for two days. Another famous street food that sold here is the "Lumpia"

name: Siulianawati Komala
review: A shop that sells gifts unique to Semarang and surrounding towns.

name: Jean Sihotang
review: tasty! must try bandeng fish, wingko babat, mochi, and many snack here. a good place for shopping local snack, food for souvenirs/gift.thankseeyou.

name: Adi Wahyu Pribadi
review: One of signature stores in Semarang. They have many processed milkfish. Delicious but pricey.

name: Suyandi Liyis
review: The center of bandeng boneless fish. And so many other things to buy as gifts

name: Andre Dharmawan
review: Seems like it's the best in town. I've just been here 3 weeks ago, and traveled to Semarang again just to buy this again. I LOVE HOW THE SECURITY WORKS!!He warned a bald guy who put his masker down. LOVED IT

name: Basilius Prabawa Brodjonegoro
review: It was very crowded but surprisingly we got what we came for relatively quickly. (You might need to learn some Indonesian queueing skills if you're a foreigner though.) The bandeng is good, but I'm not connoisseur enough to tell between one Semarang bandeng and another.

name: Nofitra Dewi Suparno P
review: The best bandeng presto ever! Price per kg is vary depend on the fish size. You can buy vacuumed one for longer shelf life.

name: Eny Buchary
review: Toko terlengkap dan terbaik yang menyediakan bandeng presto dan segala oleh2 penganan khas Semarang. This is THE place if you want to buy soft-bone (presto, high-pressure cooking) milkfish in Semarang. Prepared in various flavors that are to die for. They have several options in terms of shelf life: 24-hours, 2-days, 3-days and 5-days. Very convenient as souvenirs for families and friends. Staff are very helpful and knowledgeable. The lunpia (springrolls) are also delicious and they also have options for several shelf life. Will visit this shop again next time I visit Semarang.

name: Grace Tauladan
review: The most famous gift shop (food) from Semarang. I highly recommend the 'Bandeng Duri Lunak', you just have to fry it but it will be expired in 2 days. And there are many others delicious snacks such as moci gemini, wingko babat, mino, brownies , etc. If you are hungry, the cooked food are sold on the second floor. You must try the 'sruni' bandeng; taste a lil sour and spicy but very delicious.

name: Sejahya Sales
review: Sells delicious bandeng presto and a variety of different snacks. It is a very popular place and always crowded. Minus 1 star for not air conditioning the place. It gets very stuffy and uncomfortable after a while.

name: mas adip
review: All sorts of bandeng fish, also available other gifts from Semarang.

name: Ratih Indriyani Rakhmawati
review: Complete shops for milk fish varians and other traditional and modern cake , price also reasonable, long queue during public holidays only small parking area,

name: Revi Pragantha
review: A famous store for local foods, milk fish packed to bring back home n many other quality snacks to go..

name: Young Anggoro
review: Firstable you have to noticed that this place doesn't have enough area to parking for your vehicle. Even when you get the parking space, you have to have a good skill to park. But anyway this Place completely served many snacks originate from East of Java especially Semarang and Magelang such a Bandeng, Lumpia, getuk trio, tingting kacang, abon, serundeng, wingko and so many others

name: Glenn Zeng
review: Worth the travel between railway station and airport at this place for lunch. Nice local food, clean places and budget price.

name: Edu Juga
review: Have to stopby here.. When visit semarang, to buy bandeng fish.. And water apple.. Its their speciality here..

name: Stefanus Budianto
review: Good Store of Bandeng , The Legend at Semarang ğŸ‘

name: Tino de Den
review: i prefer their bandeng presto than other brands in this famous street. they have so many variants and taste, even the vacuumed one so they can lasts for a month. the only minus is, the parking area is so small, maybe can only have 4 to 5 suv's meanwhile hundreds of people visit this place at a time ğŸ˜ they also selling other snacks such as wingko babad, moachi/mochi, and others.

name: Ike Sukma
review: Lumpia and bandeng duri lunak so delicious, wanna more and more

name: M.Rizki Ramadhan
review: This the best place to buy traditional semarang foods, like bandeng, mochi, lumpia and others. I fall in love in Bandeng juwana and lumpia

name: willianto sudamadji
review: Great food , drop by to buy your bandeng here

name: Gemma
review: Price relatively a bit higher. Queue for bandeng like waiting to get nine basic food.

name: Roma Al Irsyad
review: one of the biggest Local food shop, so many choices of local snacks and food that you can bring back home, also we can also order by phone for delivery across the country.

name: Erryn Meliani
review: Beside buy souvernir, you should tried to dine in especially original bandeng and tongseng bandeng. Taste and the price really worth it. The problem will be parking lot, is really small.

name: Putari
review: The place quite crowded. Coming here mostly for their bandeng. Aside from the bandeng i also recommend wingko babat that sold in here. Other than that there're also another option but not speciality from Semarang. Please consider that it's difficult to find parking space in this area

name: Susan Hamsar
review: the place is clean, the price is standard, even relatively cheap, for a taste it's definitely delicious. will come here again if I visit Semarang City

name: Bayu Suteja
review: Complete choices for food and snack from semarang and mid java. Decent price. Good service.

name: Teuku Fauzan
review: For me who stays for 8 years in semarang (and still goin) , i always go to this place to buy some small gift (oleh - oleh) for my parent, i quite like the 'bandeng presto', you will see it from the name though lol.

name: Sekti Wicaksono
review: Good place for bringing gift for your family

name: Nevlin Sandimula
review: A good stop if you want to buy semarang food to bring to your home, parking space too small.

name: Hanifah Suranggana
review: Complete shop for fresh souvenir. Of course they have bandeng as the ace but you can find other food like lunpia, tahu bakso, moaci, wingko, and other kerupuk or keripik

name: ahmad anung
review: Good place to get some souvenirs

name: Olivia OliveTree
review: Complete store if you are looking for bandeng presto. Staff is very helpful and informative. They can recommend us what we we need and what we look for. (Chili sauce is not for sale, so it comes in the bandeng package, each one for each bandeng) The stock is a lot, so everything in the menu ar available. Price is good, taste is also good. If you are looking for another option of semarang food, they also provide it in here. Cashier is also helpful, she help us to differ our shopping items before check out. Parking lot is limited, so better be careful when parking because there are many small tenants in front of thr store.

name: Zidnie Mubarok
review: My fav place to buy "oleh-oleh" from Semarang, many kind of food and snacks, not just Bandeng, very crowded every weekend

name: dm ariza irviansyah
review: A lot of snack and food variety,price is fair , parking lot quite big, have a mushola (praying rokm) and rest room

name: Indra Gunawan
review: If you want to buy Lumpia and some other oleh2 in Semarang, this is the place! Friendly staf, nice place...

name: hydrangeachains x
review: Fast service in peak hours, easy to navigate and quite complete.

name: Wiyanto Kodrat
review: Nice restaurant inside the Juwana Bandeng. Try the many Bandeng ( Milk fish ) dishes and Bakmi Jawa Kuah. Service is good.

name: KAN ACC
review: the price is too expensive for me, coz right now there's a lot of softbone milkfish food that also have good taste but in cheaper price, dont know why people still search from this place..that's only in my opinion ğŸ˜‰âœŒï¸

name: Raden Arief Nugroho
review: One of the best souvenir/snacks shop in Semarang. They sell Semarang/Central Java-based snacks, delicacies, and drinks. You can also buy the famous "Bandeng Presto" (soft-boned milkfish). Price is affordable. There maybe cheaper options, but the quality of food/snack here is really maintained, no doubt. They also provide delivery services. Parking space is limited, avoid the weekends.

name: Apri'e Tan
review: Oleh oleh Bandeng is very famous, food on 2nd floor was oke, but the staff is quite slow, and my opinion, this place needs a lot of upgrade on the parking space, hahahaha

name: Firdaus Malik
review: Nice place for food souvenir from center java

name: Barry Pramudya
review: Most famous bandeng in town, dont get confused with similar bandeng nearby. The place is always packed with customers but they have limited parking, the neighbor should have change their building into parking lot, easy money, low maintenance.

name: Novita Rachmasari
review: Many variations of milkfish (bandeng) in 1st floor, restaurant in 2nd floor

name: nenes jesus
review: Pusat oleh2 Semarang . If you want to buy tradisonal food like Wingko , bandeng or Baso Tahu. Visit this place

name: Ruth Eveline
review: The store happens to be the most reliable store for local tourists purchasing oleh-oleh (bandeng, lumpia, tahu bakso), which taste quite delicious. It has a cafetaria at the second story. One thing I disliked was the slow service of the staff. This store has plenty of employees, but busy with their stuff instead of serving the customers quickly.

name: Krido Sadmoko
review: This outlet has a food souvenir at first floor and a restaurant at second floor. On this street they have two outlets, but this one with the restaurant above. The resto interioir using old style interior and it feels homy. They have many kind milkfish menu which is unique and may custoner like the menus, but they also have other Idonesian style menu such as fried eice, soto, babat gongso, sapi lada hitam etc. Try this place, will enhance you with another experience of Semarang city.

name: Jonathan Karel
review: Good place for giftsThe place is super crowded in high season

name: Wehazz
review: Love the food at the restaurant. The oleh-oleh store are served by very professional staff.

name: Farikhah Yuni
review: It's the place where you can find Bandeng Presto, the local food from Semarang. This place not only selling Bandeng Presto, but also other kind of local foods.

name: Isra Ananda Dwitama
review: Famous place to buy signature gift from semarang and complete. Parking area very small.

name: Terry
review: If you want to get the iconic Semarang food "Original Bandeng Presto" that doesn't have MSG, this is the place. The taste is delicious. They also have variety of traditional snacks here

name: TheWalkingDoctor
review: One of the most popular place at Semarang. Especially to find Semarang's traditional souvenirs. They have tons of foods and beverages variation. Prices are also affordable. They special item is the "Bandeng presto" (pressure cooked milk fish). You should try also their famous "kue Mochi".

name: Felix Nugraha
review: Average price with complete snacks for souvenirs from Semarang city

name: Gendro Purwanto
review: Always stop by to this shop whenever go to Semarang area.. its bandeng presto is my favourite. Loen pia, brownies cake and other traditional cake are also worth to taste. It's a pity that the parking lot is very limited. Hlpe rhe management will consider to have more parking lots..

name: F Iv
review: Recommended place to buy some particular / unique foods from semarang indonesia..

name: Yohanes Soleman
review: Special culinary gift from Semarang. Must Buy

name: Galih SMG
review: the most complete souvenir and snack center Parking is a bit difficult but there are already several parking areas available around they have a restaurant on the 2nd floor with a variety of special menus

name: Daud Usmanto
review: You can find many food and snack from Semarang and many other area. One stop shopping place for food gift. There's restaurant on the second floor with good taste. Must visit place for people who visit Semarang

name: Henry Erik Estrada
review: Overcrowded and hot. If you bring kids is not too comfortable shop here. Service is actually fast, only need time if you decided to vacuum your buy to prolonged the expiry date. The price will be slightly more expensive as they dont provide free vacuum pack. Tip : If you dont have parking space at least one person who can drive must stay in the car, else they will lock your car tire as the street is the most busiest in Semarang and actually it is forbidden to park in the street. Or better yet park somewhere else and walk to this place, it is what I usually do.

name: Mcey Oriz
review: If you are in semarang and looking for local traditional snacks. Just come here. For moslem please choose your snacks carefully because they also sells pork/pig snacks. Parking will be difficult in peak hours

name: novi kurniawan
review: The favourite place to buy local snacks and souvenirs when you visit to Semarang. The famous one is bandeng duri lunak. They provides good packing box to bring it to the airplane cabin. Debit and credit card is accepted. The area around the store is selling similar stuff, so you can find many options.

name: Joseph Armstrong
review: A must if you're in Semarang. Visit any of the Bandeng Juwana stores and get their fish to bring home to your friends and family. The restaurant itself is also nice. Very traditional food.

name: Hmd Zky
review: Staff are helpful, but some was not so patient to explain clearly on the menu for new customer, expecially on peak hours. Taste is good, many variants offered, they also offer vacum to extend the expected expired date.

name: Raphael Richfields
review: On stop place for bandeng shopping. With additional options for cookies and other delicacies to be bought home as a gift. In front of the store also a lumpia seller with great taste as well. Wish they had a larger parking spot.

name: Reananda Hidayat Permono
review: My first choice of 'oleh-oleh' when I'm in Semarang. Wide variety of local food, bandeng presto, lumpia, wingko babat, local chips and sambal, and local food from other places near Semarang like bakpia and gethuk Magelang. Extremely crowded during weekend.

name: Putri Prathiwi
review: Love the bandeng and sambal very crowded during holidays --------------------------------------------- Went here again in 2018 and still crowded as always. But the parking attendant is very helpful because it's difficult to bring your own car when the city is not allowing parking on the side of the road anymore. So the street is less crowded. oh If your looking for bakpia mixed with budget price, better come early in the morning when they just open

name: Silvano Hajid
review: A bit over-price, small space for parking lot.

name: Akhmad S Bakhri
review: One of the oldest "toko oleh-oleh" of Semarang, Central Java. Warm greetings when you come to the store... You will have explanation regarding the vacuum fish on how to preserve and cooking it. This one of my favorite gift shop when visit this clean and warm city

name: Guntur Dwiyadi
review: Good place to buy local food and snack. But it's hard to get parking spot, you should park your vehicle on other building or area around Pandanaran Street. Or if possible reach their other branch, you could google it. Well knowned for their softened bone (presto cooked) milk fish. You also could find other local / traditional snack like tempe chip, usus, wingko babat, ganjel rel, etc.

name: dandy sihombing
review: It is a clean place, have big parking area, full of traditional food for souvenir like bandeng presto, lumpia semarang, snacks, etc. If you dont have cash, they approve paying with debit / credit card, ovo, gopay, or you can take cash first in there because they have many ATM in different bank

name: Arifatun Milah
review: Many items in here and it much better if there are any signs for item placed in every rack so we didn't have to look one by one and simplify the customer to choose foods. The price is in average level. And also the service if I may say not the best I've ever see.

name: David Adi
review: Nice place to buy Bandeng Presto and many kind of local food for souvenirs. They have a restaurant at 2nd floor served many kinds menu of Ikan Bandeng. You should try once!

name: Wahyu Kuswidianty
review: This place is must visit when u come to semarang.. Why?.. Coz it's most famous place to buy semarang food icon, u can also try bandeng fish here .. The service is ok, staff also very helpful, so many variants here with very affordable price.. Very recommended.. Also located in the center of souvenir and semarang food icon..

name: Silvia D. Angg
review: Big store with various kinds of foods and snacks from Semarang. The lumpia is special. The service is awesome. I think it is one of the best stores in town since it is always full of visitors.

name: Abdurrasyidi Pawelloi
review: No others taste bandeng like in here..
